On Saturday, 4/30/11, we saw an old Jon Boat pinned on the rocks at the bottom of Kayakers ledge,<br/>
in the center of the drop a little bit to RR. It formed a dangerous hazard to swimmers, and we<br/>
watched as one woman swam out of her boat and right around this Nasty aluminium strainer. It is<br/>
upside down. and could pose a horrific pin for an unwary boater. On Saturday at 4,000 cfs, it could<br/>
not be seen from above. Only from looking up at the drop. As river levels drop, it could be<br/>
removed. Not sure if it will float free on it's own accord. Use caution when dropping into Kayakers<br/>
Ledge. While it is in the center, and can be avoided, swimmers could really get screwed if sucked<br/>
that way. Freddie Carter 5/2/11 </div>
